Subject: Re: [T2] cleaning hardware

On Sat, Dec 21, 2002 at 07:10:17PM -0500, dave jersey wrote:
> I was thinking that a really good way to clean all the hardware
> (nuts, bolts, misc little bits) would be to run them through my rock
> tumbler with some medium grit for a day or so.  scrub thoroughly to
> remove the grit and voila!  shiny clean pieces parts.

perhaps you could try something a little bit less abrasive? When I
used to reload ammo I used a tumbler filled with walnut shells to
clean the brass. Brass is very soft & it only gets all the powder &
dirt off the cases. Might work well for bolts as well & (hopefully)
leave a nice luster.

